This paper deals with the optimization of wireless resource allocation and UAV trajectory design for a multiple access channel, which involves communication between multiple ground users and a mobile UAV. This topic falls under the intersection of several CS sub-disciplines, including information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). However, given the focus on wireless communication and optimization, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves optimization techniques and algorithms, which could place it in cs.SY and cs.LG. Finally, the use of UAVs and the optimization of their trajectories could also make cs.AI a relevant sub-category.
